	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64267110">Eating activates a lot of growth pathway that cancer coopts. Fasting also activate autophagy. Forms of AMPK, which initiates many anti cancer and genome repair processes, can be activated with fasting. On the other hand, immune cells need energy and going extended periods of time without food compromises their function. I've found a variation of fasting, where carbs are loaded once perday in a time window, seems to be a good solution. The rest of the day I attempt to keep sugar levels normal by eating low g</div>
	</div>

